# AccessController.doPrivileged is OVERLOADED on PrivilegedAction<T> / PrivilegedExceptionAction<T>; a
# bare lambda/method-ref argument is applicable to both, so javac rejects it as "reference to
# doPrivileged is ambiguous". The fix re-emits the source's (PrivilegedAction) cast recovered from the
# invokedynamic result type. Real hits: fastjson2 DynamicClassLoader / JSONFactory.
+doPrivileged((PrivilegedAction)
+::getProtectionDomain
